<doc id="935512" wikidata="Q511603" url="?curid=935512" title="Ice hockey at the 1932 Winter Olympics">
<text>The men&#x27;s [[ice hockey]] tournament at the [[1932 Winter Olympics]] in Lake Placid, United States, was the fourth Olympic Championship, also serving as the sixth World Championships. Canada, represented by the Winnipeg Hockey Club, won its fourth consecutive Olympic gold medal and sixth consecutive World Championship. The United States secured the silver medal and Germany claimed one of its three all-time hockey medals by taking the bronze (West Germany would win a bronze medal in 1976, and Germany&#x27;s men&#x27;s team would win silver in 2018). Overall, four teams participated, with only two European associations (Germany and Poland) making the trip due to the worldwide Great Depression. The other European teams instead played at the 1932 European Championship.

==Medalists==
==Participating nations==

A total of 48&quot;(*)&quot; ice hockey players from four nations competed at the Lake Placid Games:
